body_html:
Wow. It doesn't make any sense that this PR would cause this. This is a pure-python test.

This looks just like a bug @case540 and I hit with that estimator migration he's working on.

Last time, we saw that a python module importing implementation details from estimator could cause this.

something like:

from tensorflow.contrib.estimator.python import estimator

Injects the "python" module back into the tf.contrib.estimator namespace.
But I really don't understand why this would be happening now.

Try adding "tf.contrib.estimator":["python"] to this dict.

body:
Wow. It doesn't make any sense that this PR would cause this. This is a pure-python test.

This looks just like a bug @case540 and I hit with that estimator migration he's working on.

Last time, we saw that a python module importing implementation details from estimator could cause this.

something like:

```
from tensorflow.contrib.estimator.python import estimator 
```

Injects the "python" module back into the `tf.contrib.estimator` namespace.
But I really don't understand why this would be happening now.

Try adding `"tf.contrib.estimator":["python"]` to [this dict](https://github.com/yifeif/tensorflow/blob/cherrypicks_IJGFA/tensorflow/tools/docs/generate_lib.py#L228).
